value.text: Stately, plump Buck Mulligan came from the stairhead, bearing a bowl of lather on which a mirror and a razor lay crossed.

It covers simply one single day, from after sun-up to near sun-up the day after, in the life of a middle-aged man, Leopold Bloom, his wife Molly, and a recent college graduate, Stephen Dedalus. It is June 16, 1904, a sunny day in Dublin.
I said yes I will Yes.
The novel is constructed as a modern parallel to Homer’s Odyssey.
